oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Time Of The Preacher - Willie Nelson performance - 1975-02-00; Red Headed Stranger - Willie Nelson performance - 1975-02-00
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Performance of Time Of The Preacher, written by Willie Nelson, produced by Willie Nelson, recorded in February 1975 at Autumn Sound Studio in Garland, TX, released by Columbia in August 1975, and performed by Willie Nelson (vocal and guitar), Bee Spears (bass), Billy English (drums), Bucky Meadows (guitar), Mickey Raphael (harmonica), and Bobbie Nelson (piano). Performance of Red Headed Stranger, written by Carl Stutz and Edith Lindeman Calisch, produced by Willie Nelson, recorded in February 1975 at Autumn Sound Studio in Garland, TX, released by Columbia in August 1975, and performed by Willie Nelson (vocal and guitar), Bee Spears (bass), Billy English (drums), Bucky Meadows (guitar), Mickey Raphael (harmonica), and Bobbie Nelson (piano).
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Willie Nelson
